---
import InnerLayout from '../layouts/InnerLayout.astro';
const schema = {"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"Privacy Policy","url":"https://anyinterview.to/privacy","dateModified":"2026-05-01"};
---
<InnerLayout title="Privacy Policy — AnyInterview" description="How AnyInterview collects, uses, and protects your data. Written to be actually readable." schema={schema} canonical="https://anyinterview.to/privacy">
  <section class="ip-hero">
    <div class="ip-hero-inner">
      <p class="ip-eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Your privacy, <em>plainly stated.</em></h1>
      <p class="ip-hero-sub">We believe privacy policies should be readable by humans. This one is.</p>
      <p class="ip-last-updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="ip-section">
    <div class="ip-section-inner--narrow">
      <div class="ip-prose">

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Account information: name, email address, company name, and billing details when you create an account.</li>
          <li>Interview data: recordings, transcripts, and AI-generated summaries from interviews you create and conduct.</li>
          <li>Participant data: voice recordings, responses, and consent timestamps from interview participants (see "Interview participant data" below).</li>
          <li>Usage data: how you interact with the product — pages visited, features used, session duration — collected via PostHog analytics.</li>
          <li>Device and browser data: IP address, browser type, and operating system, collected automatically when you use the service.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we use it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To operate and deliver the service — your interviews, transcripts, and dashboard.</li>
          <li>To improve the product — we analyze aggregate usage patterns to understand what's working and what isn't.</li>
          <li>To communicate with you — product updates, billing notices, support replies.</li>
          <li>We never use your interview data to train third-party AI models. See our subprocessors list at <a href="/subprocessors">/subprocessors</a> for the AI providers we use.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your data. We share it only with the sub-processors needed to deliver the service — infrastructure, transcription, payments, and analytics. The full list is at <a href="/subprocessors">/subprocessors</a>.</p>
        <p>We may disclose data if required by law or to respond to a valid legal process. We will notify you when legally permitted to do so.</p>

        <h2>Interview participant data</h2>
        <p>When you send an interview link to a participant, they are the data subject — you are the data controller, and we are the data processor for that data.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Participants receive an AI-interview disclosure before the session begins. Their consent is required to proceed.</li>
          <li>Consent timestamps are stored immutably alongside the transcript.</li>
          <li>Participants may request access to or deletion of their data by contacting you (the customer) or us at <a href="mailto:privacy@anyinterview.to">privacy@anyinterview.to</a>.</li>
          <li>Recordings are stored per your account's retention settings (default: 7 years for compliance customers, 2 years for standard).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on where you are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>GDPR (EEA/UK): Right to access, rectification, erasure, portability, and to object to processing. Email <a href="mailto:privacy@anyinterview.to">privacy@anyinterview.to</a>.</li>
          <li>CCPA (California): Right to know what data we've collected, right to deletion, and right to opt out of sale (we don't sell your data).</li>
          <li>COPPA: This service is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a child has provided data, contact us and we will delete it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Account data: retained for the life of your account plus 30 days after termination.</li>
          <li>Interview data: configurable per account. Default retention is 2 years for Pro, 7 years for compliance-tier customers.</li>
          <li>Usage analytics: retained for 12 months in aggregate form.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>Interview data is encrypted with AES-256 at rest and TLS 1.3 in transit. For a full overview of our security posture, see <a href="/security">/security</a>.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:privacy@anyinterview.to">privacy@anyinterview.to</a>. We respond within 30 days.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <style>
    .ip-last-updated { font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-mute); margin-top: 12px; }
  </style>
</InnerLayout>
